        "management": "Initiate two-drug therapy. Preferred combinations: ACEi/ARB + CCB, or ACEi/ARB + thiazide diuretic. Avoid ACEi + ARB combination. If black patients, use CCB + thiazide. Add third agent if BP not at target. Check compliance and consider secondary causes if resistant."
