        "management": "Confirm adherence and accurate measurement. Use 24h ABPM. Maximize diuretic (chlorthalidone 25-50mg or torsemide if CKD). Add MRA (spironolactone 25-50mg or eplerenone). Screen for secondary causes: plasma aldosterone/renin ratio, sleep study, renal artery imaging, metanephrines. Consider referral to hypertension specialist."
